codex
Plan:
1. Build a self-contained verifier contract that discovers a real trapped LP balance in the zap from on-chain state, instead of hardcoding a pair.
2. Encode the exploit path exactly: obtain a small withdrawable LP position for that same pair, call vulnerable `withdraw(..., tokenOut = pair, basketId = 0)`, and capture the unrelated LP transferred out of the zap.
3. Prefer direct use of any verifier-held underlying balance; if none exists, fall back to a minimal same-pair flash-swap to seed the deposit without changing the exploit causality.
4. Realize net profit after temporary capital repayment by burning only the minimum stolen LP needed to repay the flash swap, leaving residual LP as profit.
5. Compile-check the Solidity locally and iterate on any interface or syntax issues before handing off the final `src/FlawVerifier.sol`.
